text=From: [[OSX Daily -> http://osxdaily.com/2011/01/26/change-the-screenshot-save-file-location-in-mac-os-x/]]%0a%0a!!Change the Screenshot Save File Location in Mac OS X%0aMac OS X, Tips & Tricks - January 26th, 2011%0a%0a[[#excerpt]]%0aBy default, anytime you take a screen capture in Mac OS X it will save the screenshot file to the current users desktop. You can adjust where Mac OS X saves a captured screenshot to any other location, here is how to do this:%0a[[#excerptend]]%0a%0aLaunch Terminal and use the following syntax:%0a%0a  defaults write com.apple.screencapture location /path/%0a%0aFor example, if I want to have the screenshots appear in my Pictures folder, I would use:%0a%0a  defaults write com.apple.screencapture location ~/Pictures/%0a%0aTo have the changes take effect, you then must type:%0a%0a  killall `SystemUIServer%0a%0aSo the next time you take a screenshot (or as Windows converts like to say, Print Screen on a Mac), the screenshot file will appear at the location you specified.%0a%0aYou can change the saved screenshot location back to the default setting by specifying the desktop again:%0a%0a  defaults write com.apple.screencapture location ~/Desktop/%0a%0aAgain, you’d need to kill `SystemUIServer for changes to take effect.%0a%0a(:Summary:How to have your screen captures put into a different directory than the Desktop:)(:Crumbs:[[Main/]] | [[ComputerStuff]]:)(:Parent:AppleStuff:)(:Categories:[[!ComputerStuff]]:)(:Tags: osx, mac, changing defaults:)%0a%0a(:Summary:How to have your screen captures saved into a different directory than the Desktop:)%0a(:Parent:(Technology.)OSX:)%0a(:IncludeMe:[[(Technology.)OSX]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!Articles]]:)%0a(:Tags: screenshots, osx:)%0a(:tags-hide screenshots, osx :)%0a
